Two different subjects in one topic (or is that the other way around).

Anyway, how does one achieve the following:

1. An extra domain for a Cleric. I know of the following ways:

- Bonus Domain (epic feat from ELH): one extra domain from the one
available to your deity
- Domain Draught (magic item from DMG II): basically a "potion" that
works only once, not what I'm looking for
- Divine Oracle (prestige class from CDiv): this gives one fixed
domain, not sure which, IDHTBIFOM
- Radiant Servant (prestige class from CDiv): get an extra 'Pelor'
domain, provided you have the Sun domain first; perhaps what I'm
looking for, but not sure.

Any other ways?

2. Flight for a Half-Dragon (a Medium one; a Large one gets his
'draconic wings' anyway). You can of course cast /Fly/ on him or give
him Winged Boots or Wings of Flying, but these cost him a standard
action to activate. Is there perhaps a feat, maybe in Draconomicon or
some such, to give a (Medium) Half-Dragon his wings, or a feat to make
him 'Large' or count as Large or something like that?
